CETAF is the Consortium of European Taxonomic Facilities: a European network of Natural Science Museums, Natural History Museums, Botanical Gardens and Research Centers with their associated biological collections and research expertise.&#xd;
&#xd;
The CETAF network comprises 60 of the largest taxonomic institutions from 21 European countries. Its member institutions hold biological collections and conduct taxonomic research.&#xd;
&#xd;
CETAF also cooperates with organisations such as GBIF, IUCN, UNEP, CBD, among the most important.
